<p>The mural <em>Peace Flowers</em> by Tom Cech can be found on the wall of the Cineplex to the north of the Aberdeen Plaza. &nbsp;The work evokes moments in history when Canada and Belgium crossed paths and relied on each other in matters of peace and war. It is a tribute to our countries’ friendship and like-mindedness. It artistically depicts two symbolic “Belgian” flowers – the <strong>“Peace Rose of Ghent” </strong>and the <strong>“Poppy of Flanders Fields” </strong>as well as two inspiring Canadian figures – painter <strong>Mary Riter Hamilton </strong>and WWI officer and poet <strong>John McCrae</strong>.</p>
